		"description": "<article><p>None living know who or what Dal was, only that the name is carved into this device. About half a foot in diameter, this flat disk resembles a sundial with many styles (time-telling edges), each of which can be moved on its own course, rotating on the flat of the disc on an undetectable groove. As these are moved, you receive a vision of events and emotions that have occurred in your current location.</p><p>As an action, you can use the dial of Dal to cast the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.24rmiwo0w5pd746x]{Legend Lore} spell focused on your current location without the need for material components. Once used in this way, the dial cannot be used again until you finish a long rest.</p></article>",
